Comments: Modern assemblage. R. boreale (ca. 5% in this sample) is a species reported from the Antarctic continental shelf by Nishimura et al. (1997), and also associated with high productivity in a coastal environment.
Only two radiolarian specimens in two slides, both extant species. Abundant quartz and biotite fragments. Trace sponge spicules
